children.subject: Hey, thanks for the response! Sent you a friend request, but I can't seem to send messages to you since it seems like I have to be your friend/have mutual servers. My Discord username is laserbird#4896 just to clarify. Also, if anyone else is interested in a group, feel free to add/message me on Discord too!

Hi, I'm also taking cs162 this summer and am interested in joining or forming a group! I'm minoring in CS but I have finished all my major requirements so I'll have lots of time to grind on the projects. I have not taken 61C, but I've been learning/reviewing the 61C material before 162 starts. This is because of the new policies — I won't be able to take 162 in Fall as a CS minor, so I can only take it over the summer, before 61C. But I've received As in all previous coursework and I always work really hard on projects.

I'll be between SF and Berkeley over the summer so I can definitely do in-person or online meetings as well. Please message me on Discord if you're interested! My tag is redj#1584

history.content: Hello! I'm an EECS major taking cs162 this summer. I'll be on campus for the summer, so I'm flexible with both in-person or online meetings, preferably in-person. Planning on reviewing and preparing before class starts if anyone wants to join me and willing to grind on projects. Wondering if anyone is also looking for a group or has openings in their group. Feel free to comment below if interested and I can shoot you an email. Thanks!
